dc_title_s: Map of Michigan, Wisconsin, Minnesota, and Iowa.
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.   "12"--Lower right.   Though likely produced in 1873, county boundaries shown date from some time in the 1860s.   Likely from: The people's pictorial atlas / Jones and Hamilton, 1873.|42 x 30 centimeters|Scale approximately 1:3,500,000|General Map Collection
